abstract: JPMorgan Chase said on Friday that its first-quarter profit rose 33 percent to $6.5 billion. | Prosecutors filed insider trading charges against Scott I. London, a former senior executive at the accounting giant KPMG. | Joh. A. Benckiser agreed to pay $9.8 billion for D.E Master Blenders 1753, a European coffee company. | Cameron and Tyler Winklevoss have built up a sizable position in bitcoins.
